## 12\. Termination of the License

- 12.1. **Breach**: This **License** and the rights granted hereunder (including
  copyright and patent licenses) will terminate automatically and immediately
  with respect to **You** upon any breach by **You** of the terms of this
  License.
- 12.2. **Patent Litigation**: Termination of patent rights under Article 2.3 is
  immediate upon filing of the specified patent litigation and is not subject to
  the cure provisions below for other breaches.
- 12.3. **Effect on Downstream Recipients**: Such termination will not terminate
  the licences of any person who has received the Work from **You** under this
  License, provided such persons remain in full compliance with this License.
  Rights of compliant downstream recipients are not retroactively revoked.
- 12.4. **Survival**: Provisions which, by their nature, must remain in effect
  beyond the termination of this **License** shall survive, including but not
  limited to Articles 1 (Definitions, to the extent necessary for interpreting
  surviving provisions), 2.2 (Patent Grant, for grants made prior to
  termination, subject to Art 2.3), 6.4 (No Warranty for External Works), 7
  (Disclaimer of Warranty), 8 (Limitation of Liability), 9 (Additional
  Agreements, regarding indemnification), 13 (Miscellaneous), 14 (Dispute
  Resolution and Jurisdiction), and 15 (Applicable Law).
- 12.5. **Cure and Reinstatement**: For breaches other than those covered by
  Article 2.3, if **You** cure the breach within thirty (30) days of becoming
  aware of it (or receiving notice of it from **Land** or a copyright holder),
  Your license is reinstated provisionally. If **You** are notified of the
  breach by **Land** or a copyright holder, and this is Your first notification
  of a breach of this License, Your license is reinstated permanently if the
  breach is cured within thirty (30) days of such notice. If this is not Your
  first notification of a breach, or if the breach is not cured within thirty
  (30) days, Your license is permanently terminated. Reinstatement beyond these
  provisions is at the sole discretion of the copyright holders of the Work.

